# CrokTile Slides Repo Conventions

## Project Context
CrokTile is a GPU programming framework. This repo manages all presentation slides using Marp (Markdown -> PDF/PPTX/HTML).

## Directory Structure
- `decks/<deck-name>/slides.md` — Each slide deck lives in its own folder
- `decks/<deck-name>/dist/` — Build outputs (PDF/PPTX/HTML), gitignored
- `themes/` — Reusable Marp CSS themes (croktile-dark, croktile-light, croktile-cn)
- `templates/` — Slide structure templates (tech-talk, product-pitch, weekly-report)
- `assets/images/` — Shared images and logos

## Creating a New Deck
1. Create `decks/<deck-name>/slides.md`
2. Use Marp frontmatter: `marp: true`, `theme: croktile-dark`, `paginate: true`
3. Reference templates in `templates/` for structural guidance
4. Reference logos via relative path: `![](../../assets/images/logo-square.svg)`

## Available Themes
- `croktile-dark` — Dark theme, best for tech talks and conferences
- `croktile-light` — Light theme, best for formal/business presentations
- `croktile-cn` — Chinese-optimized, Noto Serif SC headings, wider line-height

## Marp Slide Syntax Quick Reference
- `---` separates slides
- `<!-- _class: lead -->` for title/centered slides
- `<!-- _class: split -->` for two-column layout
- `![width:300](path)` for sized images
- `![bg](path)` for background images
- `![bg right:40%](path)` for split background

## Building / Exporting
```bash
export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"
# Single deck (--no-stdin required in non-interactive shells)
npx marp --no-stdin decks/<name>/slides.md -o decks/<name>/dist/slides.html
npx marp --no-stdin decks/<name>/slides.md -o decks/<name>/dist/slides.pdf
npx marp --no-stdin decks/<name>/slides.md -o decks/<name>/dist/slides.pptx

# Batch build all decks
uv run python scripts/build.py

# Preview with live reload
npx marp --no-stdin decks/<name>/slides.md --preview
```

## Style Guidelines
- Use `h1` for slide titles, `h2` for subtitles, `h3` for section labels
- Keep slides concise: max 6-8 bullet points per slide
- Use code blocks with language tags for syntax highlighting
- Use tables for comparisons and metrics
- Include CrokTile logo on title slides
